    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Seat Belts- Two Point (Optional)</title>
        <para>When the Two Point Seat Belt option is required the seat track option is also required. (
            <hotlnk document="s47003_21.xml" xrefid="f4700366">Figure 66, Item 1</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The seat belt mounting is to the seat frame</para>
            <figure id="f47003164" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003164.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003164.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="232px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 164. Two Point Seat Belt Seat Frame Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SEAT BELT ANCHOR AND MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SEAT BACK CUSHION</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">UNDER SEAT HEATER (NOT ALL SEATS)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SEAT FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SEAT CUSHION (SHOWN TILTED FORWARD)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SEAT BELTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To remove the lap belt assemblies, disengage the securing clip.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tilt the seat cushion forward, locate the seat belt mounting bolts and nuts on the seat
                    frame.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the lock nuts and washers, remove the mounting bolts.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the seat belt assemblies.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Before re-installing the seat belt assemblies, check the belts for chafing and or
                    wear.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The two point seat belt assemblies with handicap application use the seat track assemblies
                for fastening and securing the seat belts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the seat belt assembly to be removed, loosen and remove the floor mounted track stud
                bolt lock nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the lock nut removed, lift the seat belt mounting end from the floor stud.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the floor stud, slide stud forward and lift from track.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
